    "learning_outcomes": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": "For the degree of Bachelor of Arts in Urban Studies & Planning, Policy & Planning Concentration"
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": "Students who complete a degree in the Department of Urban and Regional Planning will be able to:"
      },
      {
        "type": "list",
        "list_type": "ol",
        "content": [
          "Identify and understand the planners’ role in:\n\t\nadvocating for racial and economic equity;\nplanning for the needs of disadvantaged groups;\nexpanding choice and opportunity;\nreducing inequities through critical evaluation of systems and institutions;\nplanning for sustainable communities;\nreducing impacts of climate change; and\ncreating equitable and climate‐adapted futures.",
          "Demonstrate planning proficiency in a global context in the areas of: \n\t\nhistory, theory, law and institutions;\nthe evolution of the practice of planning; and\nurban and regional development.",
          "Build and put into practice a set of skills that are central to the planning profession, including skills specific to:\n\t\ncommunication, community engagement, and the planning process;\nresearch and critical thinking;\nmapping and data visualization; and\ndata collection and analysis, and data analytics.",
          "Illustrate professional leadership values including collaborative skills and ethical behavior in research, client representation and decision-making."
        ]
      }
